(873, 42, 0, '<p>Samas Beach is located at the west of Parangtritis beach, at Srigading village, District of Sanden, about 14<br>kilometres south of Bantul. From downtown Yogyakarta, you could travel to the southwest for 35 kilometres to<br>get to the beach. Samas Beach is easy to visit with private or public vehicles.</p>\r\n<p>In the beach there are many estuaries which form into lake and used as a place for<br>cultivating fresh-water fish and shrimp. Besides its beauty, the specialty of this beach is sea turtles. Samas beach<br>is a beach often visited by sea turtles of many kinds like the Hawksbills sea turtle, the leatherbacks sea turtle, and<br>the green sea turtle. Those sea turtles come at a certain time and during the egg-laying season.</p>\r\n<p>In this beach you will find a conservation area of sea turtle as a concern from the society and the government<br>toward this endangered species. In the conservation area, you will find a pool for the sea turtles’ babies. The babies<br>will be kept in the conservation to avoid them from the predators, until it reached certain age and ready to be<br>released to the sea.</p>\r\n<p>Besides seeing the sea turtles in the conservation, you can also go to the lake which is formed from the<br>rivers estuaries to fishing, or perhaps to ride boat in the lagoon. This beach is suitable as a natural tourist object<br>where you can enjoy the nature’s beauty, learn about the sea turtle or simply refresh your mind with your friends<br>or family.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>How many kinds of turtle are mentioned in the text?</p>', 'Try Out 2', '<p>Nine.</p>', '<p>Five.</p>', '<p>Three.</p>', '<p>Two.</p>', '', '', '', '2', '', '3', 'main'),
